Someone has some code that runs at 4ms and uses a different algorithm.  My code ran at 7ms.  I like this faster code.  It still uses the trick of creating a fixed value table only once per SUBMIT, then the other test cases can use that generated table.  This code show a different and better method for initializing a fixed value table called `mults[]`, from the method used in the above code for `pascalsTriangle[][]`.
