The code initializes the dp vector with binomial coefficients in O(n^2) time, where n is the size of the input array.
The sol function is called recursively, and at each recursion level, it splits the array into two parts, which takes O(n) time.
Overall, the time complexity of the code is O(n^3) because the sol function is called recursively for each element in the array, and calculating binomial coefficients takes O(n^2) time.
- Space complexity:
