# Approach
As mention in the problem we have to find the number of ways to reorder the given array which generates the same tree.
The first element can not be rearranged because if we change its position the tree will change.

The dfs function is a recursive helper function that takes in the nums array and a 2D vector comb as input. It performs a depth-first search to calculate the number of different reorderings.

The base case for the recursion is when the size of the nums array is less than or equal to 2. In this case, there is only one way to reorder the elements, so the function returns 1.

If the size of the nums array is greater than 2, the function continues with the recursive approach. It splits the nums array into two parts: left and right. The left array contains all the elements smaller than the first element of nums, and the right array contains all the elements greater than the first element.

